Aimery's first wife, Eschiva of Ibelin, was the elder daughter of Baldwin of Ibelin, Lord of Mirabel and Ramleh, and Richelda of Beisan.{{sfn|Hamilton|2000|p=35}}{{sfn|Runciman|1989a|p=423, Appendix III: Genealogical trees, Number 4.}} Their children:
*Burgundia, married [[Walter of Montbéliard]], who was regent for her younger brother, Hugh I of Cyprus, from 1205 to 1210.{{sfn|Runciman|1989b|p=134, Appendix III: Genealogical trees, Number 1.}} 
*[[Helvis of Lusignan (1190-1218)|Helvis]], was the wife of [[Raymond-Roupen]],{{sfn|Runciman|1989b|p=138, Appendix III: Genealogical trees, Number 1.}} who was [[Prince of Antioch]] from 1216 to 1219. 
*Guy, died young{{sfn|Runciman|1989b|p=84}}
*John, died young{{sfn|Runciman|1989b|p=84}}
*[[Hugh I of Cyprus|Hugh I]], married [[Alice of Champagne]]{{sfn|Runciman|1989b|p=84}}

Aimery's second wife, Isabella I of Jerusalem, was the only daughter of Amalric I of Jerusalem and [[Maria Komnene, Queen of Jerusalem|Maria Komnene]]. Their children: 
*[[Sybilla of Lusignan|Sybilla]], was the second wife of [[Leo I, King of Armenia]].{{sfn|Runciman|1989b|p=95, Appendix III: Genealogical trees, Number 1. and 4.}} 
*[[Melisende of Lusignan|Melisende]] married [[Bohemond IV of Antioch]].{{sfn|Runciman|1989b|p=95, Appendix III: Genealogical trees, Number 1-2.}} 
* a son died in childhood, 2 February 1205.{{sfn|Runciman|1989b|p=103}}

